3. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The paper does not focus on distributed, parallel, or cluster computing, but it does discuss the impact of varying demands and capacity on switch schemes, which could be relevant to distributed computing. 
4. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper does not explicitly deal with information theory, but it does discuss the impact of varying demands and capacity on network performance, which could be relevant to information theory. 
5. cs.CC (Computational Complexity) - The paper does not deal with computational complexity, but it does discuss the impact of varying demands and capacity on switch schemes, which could be relevant to computational complexity in network design.
